180 grams Orzo
90 grams British Smoked Bacon Lardons
120 grams Sliced Mushrooms
60 grams Mature Cheddar Cheese
10 grams Chicken Stock Paste
75 grams Creme Fraiche
20 grams Grated Hard Italian Style Cheese
25 grams Sun-Dried Tomato Paste
20 grams Wild Rocket
100 milliliter(s) Water for the Sauce

Boil a full kettle.
Pour it into a saucepan with 1/2 tsp salt on high heat.
Boil the orzo, 10 mins.
Once cooked, drain, pop back in the pan and drizzle with oil.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a frying pan on high heat.
Once hot, fry the bacon and mushrooms, 5-6 mins. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Cook bacon thoroughly.
Meanwhile, grate the Cheddar.

Next, stir in the chicken stock paste, creme fraiche and water (see pantry).
Simmer, 2-3 mins. Remove from the heat.
Stir in the Cheddar, hard Italian style cheese, sun-dried tomato paste and orzo. Toss to coat.

Share the orzo between your bowls.
Top with the rocket leaves.
Enjoy!